                        <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440304-996-offence-1 t18440304-geo-10"></join>St. Matthew, Bethnal-green</placeName>, ant steal<lb></lb>ing 4 pinafores, value 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 5 handkerchiefs, 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and 1 sheet, 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; his good.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-918" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-918" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-918" type="surname" value="REEVES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-918" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM REEVES</persName>
                  </hi>. At half-past two o'clock on Friday afternoon, the 1st of March, I was working on a piece of ground opposite Mr. Higgins's house—I saw the prisoner and another boy loitering about a long while—I saw the prisoner get on a window sill near Mr. Higgins's—he tried to force the window down ten or twelve times, but could not—he then went to Mr. Higgins's house, and got on the sill, and tried to get the window down—he forced down the top sash, and unfastened the bottom one, and then <hi rend="italic">shoved</hi> them both up together—he went and fetched his companion, who had a bag, from the corner of the street—the prisoner went to the window, jumped in, and the other boy was holding the bag outside—he handed the things out to him—I then went and caught the prisoner, who ran away—I brought him back to Mr. Higgins's shop—I am sure he is the boy.</p>
               <p>
